usage: ./percolation -p <prob> -s|-b [-m -l <siz> -t <arg>]

options:
-p <prob>		Probability (bond/site)
-b 			Use Bond percolation
-s			Use Site percolation
-l <siz>		Lattice size (DEFAULT : 1024*1024)
-m 			Use multithreading. solves sequentially in NOT SPECIFIED!
-t <arg>		Specify what type of percolation to search:
					[0] A cluster that spans all rows.
					[1] A cluster that spans all columns.
					[2] A cluster that spans all rows and cols.

